      <part part_index="2" name="Hong Kong-Asia's art capital" page="0" source="2">
      	<article allWordsNum="125">
            	<![CDATA[
Hong Kong is known as a city of trade and finance.Now, it is discovering a new role as Asia's art capital.
The city became the world's third largest art auction market(艺术品拍卖市场) after New York and London in 2007 and since 2008 it has been home to a successful modern art fair.
Hong Kong is also attracting big-name art galleries(画廊) to compete against London's Tate Modern(泰特现代美术馆) or New York's Museum of Modern Art.
However, Hong Kong does face a lot of challenges(挑战).It lacks a museum or art education place that encourages the development of modern art.Meanwhile, its artist community is small and faces high costs.It's not easy for artists to find cheap studios there.It's still a long way for Hong Kong to become a first-class art capital in the world.
            	]]>
            </article>
